fields.value: Photo Ratings of CAPS Participants (CAPS-PHOTORAT CAPS-PHOTOGR and CAPS-PHOTOST module)

dsDescriptionValue.value:
In this unit, Rs are asked to check out a photo album and to rate 24 of the photos contained in it on 4 100-point scales: homely/ good-looking, lazy/studious, ignorant/intelligent, argumentative/ agreeable. The 24 photos rated by each R include his/her own photo and those of their three CAPS team members. (It is possible that Rs may not realize that they are rating their team members because no identification by name or group membership is made and many Rs have not met their team members face -to-face.)

Each photograph is rated by approximately 24 respondents. No standard scoring. Add photo number of ratee, and SIDs of rated Rs. The PHOTOST file in CAPS86 contains the same data, with the ratings standardized by rater and stored by ratee.
